Usage: getHierFlowMode [-help] [-budgets] [-quiet] [-nonDefault]

-help                                    # Prints out the command usage
-budgets                                 # This will set budgeting mode options
                                         # via setBudgetingMode command for
                                         # accurate or preliminary budgeting
                                         # whichever is specified. It has lower
                                         # precedence than other user specified
                                         # budgeting mode settings.
                                         # (enums={accurate preliminary none}, default=none)
-quiet                                   # Displays the current settings in Tcl list format only
-nonDefault                              # Displays the current settings which are not default settings